 <text>
  <front>
   <head>A SONG.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="octet">
     <l n="1" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">was sprightly and gay;</l>
     <l n="2" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">Had the Bloom of Fifteen on her Cheek:</l>
     <l n="3" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">Her Lovers came flocking each Day,</l>
     <l n="4" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">And a thousand fond Things they wou'd speak.</l>
     <l n="5" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">She, giddy and thoughtless, gave Ear</l>
     <l n="6" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">To the Tale of each flattering Tongue;</l>
     <l n="7" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">And thought she was blest, to appear</l>
     <l n="8" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">In a Circle of Lovers so young.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="octet">
     <l n="9" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">elate with the Conquests she gain'd,</l>
     <l n="10" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">She neglected to act with a Grace;</l>
     <l n="11" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">And thought that her Triumph for Life,</l>
     <l n="12" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">Was secure by the Charms of her Face.</l>
     <l n="13" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">While , more modest and coy,</l>
     <l n="14" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">Not a Lover yet boasts in her Train;</l>
     <l n="15" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">Which  with Pleasure observ'd,</l>
     <l n="16" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">And delighted to give the Nymph Pain.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="octet">
     <l n="17" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">Lovers grew cold and dropp'd off,</l>
     <l n="18" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">As her Folly increas'd with her Years;</l>
     <l n="19" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">When Time had her Beauty defac'd,</l>
     <l n="20" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">They left her to Wrinkles and Tears.</l>
     <l n="21" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">While  took Care to supply</l>
     <l n="22" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">With each Grace the swift Conquest of Time;</l>
     <l n="23" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">And was much more belov'd in Decay,</l>
     <l n="24" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">Than  was e'er in her Prime.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="octet">
     <l n="25" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">Mind, with each Virtue replete,</l>
     <l n="26" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">Had enamour'd a right-judging Swain;</l>
     <l n="27" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">Who sought her to make them both blest:</l>
     <l n="28" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">And still is unrivall'd her Reign.</l>
     <l n="29" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">All ye fair, that attend to my Song,</l>
     <l n="30" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">Be ye warned by  ill Fate;</l>
     <l n="31" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">Think the Graces to Beauty belong;</l>
     <l n="32" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">Lest forsaken, you court them too late.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
